The test software for motion perception was custom-developed for these experiments and consists of two separate modules, one for stimulus generation and another for running the actual test program. Since threshold measurements are much faster and more reliable using four-alternative forced choice than two-alternative forced choice tasks, we employed four directions of motion (up, down, left, and right) to be discriminated by the subject. The stimuli were plaids composed of two orthogonal Gabor patterns of 45° left and right tilt [15]:
